---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css'
// Welcome to Astro! Wondering what to do next? Check out the Astro documentation at https://docs.astro.build
// Don't want to use any of this? Delete everything in this file, the `assets`, `components`, and `layouts` directories, and start fresh.
const pageTitle = "About me";

const identity = {
  firstName: "Ryan",
  country: "USA",
  occupation: "Software Engineer",
  hobbies: ["Reading", "3D-Printing", "Weight Training"]
}

const skills = ["HTML", "CSS", "Javascript", "Python", "Java", "C++"]
const happy = true;
const finished = false;
const goal = 3;

const skillColor = "crimson";
const fontWeight = "bold";
const textCase = "uppercase";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle="About Me">
  <div class="main-content">
    <p>Hi!! Welcome to my blog. Started this year, <span class="year">2026</span></p>

    <p>
      Began this as a way to practice maintaining something. I am not quite sure how this blog will evolve in the future but
      to even iterate on something, one has to begin. I hope to share projects, memories, or track hobbies on here. 
    </p>

    <p>
      I have spent a majority of my life moving around, when I was younger I would end up moving schools almost yearly, until about the 4th grade where
      my family decided to set roots in Southern California. From there I went on to graduate with a <span class="degree">Bachelors of Science
      in Computer Science from California State University Northridge.</span> Where I would meet many
      people who heavily influence any hobbies or adventures found on this blog.
    </p>

    <p>
      From there I began work as a Software Developer for a Mid-size Finance company and am currently <a href="mailto:ryan.gwood282@gmail.com">open to work!</a> Other hobbies I have include: 
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>The gym where the intesity varies month to month</li>
      <li>Along with cooking habit where I hope to find a new appreciation for food I have claimed to dislike in the past</li>
      <li>A reading habit that has allowed me to explore many new areas/worlds without needing to travel far</li>
      <li>Homelabbing that has greatly enabled me to explore new technologies relating to programming</li>
    </ul>
  
  </div>
  

</BaseLayout>
    

    

<style is:global define:vars={{skillColor, fontWeight, textCase}}>
  h1 {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: 4rem;
  }

  .skill {
    color: var(--skillColor);
    font-weight: var(--fontWeight);
    text-transform: var(--textCase);
  }

  .main-content{
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    max-width: 65ch;
	  padding: 2rem 2rem 4rem;
    gap: 2rem;
    background-color: var(--storm);
    color: var(--stone);
    margin: 1rem;
  }

  p{
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--rain)
  }

  .year{
    color: var(--petal)
  }

  .degree{
    color: var(--clay)
  }

  li:before{
    content: "â€¢ ";
    color: var(--rain)
  }
  ul{
    list-style: none;
    font-size: .85rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
</style>